TXT_SWITCH_NOMOVE: Toggle No-move Mode
TXT_SWITCH_NOMOVE_DESC: If the action the unit is about to perform differs from the mouse action, and the action would cause the unit to move near the target, whether to change that action to Guard.
TXT_DISTR_SPREAD: Target Distribution Range
TXT_DISTR_SPREAD_DESC: In target distribution mode, range 0 is default game behavior; hotkeys can set range to 4, 8, or 16 cells, then selected units will distribute targets evenly within range. Only when the unit's action matches mouse action will it distribute; otherwise fallback to default (no air units). An indicator circle shows range. You can also adjust range by mouse wheel while holding the toggle key.
TXT_DISTR_FILTER: Target Distribution Filter
TXT_DISTR_FILTER_DESC: Mode `None` is default; with non-zero range, a green circle appears. Hotkeys change mode to:
  - `Like` – select targets with same armor class (blue circle)
  - `Type` – select targets of same type (infantry, vehicle, building) (yellow circle)
  - `Name` – select targets of same name or `GroupAs` (red circle)
TXT_DISTR_HOLDDOWN: Target Distribution Mode Toggle
TXT_DISTR_HOLDDOWN_DESC: Hold this hotkey and use mouse wheel to adjust target distribution range
MSG:DistributionModeOn: Target Distribution Mode: On
MSG:DistributionModeOff: Target Distribution Mode: Off
